## ARTICLE 1 — OWNERSHIP AND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY

### 1.1 Exclusive Ownership
The Software, in its entirety and in each of its constituent parts, is the exclusive intellectual property of Darkden64. This ownership includes but is not limited to:

- All source code, in any programming language, including TypeScript, JavaScript, and any configuration files
- All algorithms, logic flows, and computational methods, including but not limited to the Zen-Eco gamification engine, the XP economy system, the freshnessScore calculation engine, the streak multiplier system, and the Power Cards mechanism
- All data structures, Firestore database schemas, AsyncStorage key architectures, and data pipeline designs
- The Barcode Analytics V2 pipeline, including the EAN-level behavioral indexing system, the meal slot classification algorithm, and all associated aggregation logic
- The Local First Cloud Sync architecture, including the dual-write mechanism, the `isStorageLoaded` guard pattern, and the conflict resolution strategy
- The Family Fridge synchronization system, including the invite code generation mechanism, the anti-bruteforce logic, and the `unsubscribeFamilyRef` logout flow
- The GDPR Kill-Switch implementation and all associated privacy-by-design patterns
- The CO₂ hybrid calculation engine combining Agribalyse data with Open Food Facts category fallbacks
- All user interface designs, screen layouts, color schemes, typography choices, component architectures, and visual identities
- All business strategies, monetization roadmaps, data valuation models, and client targeting analyses contained in any document associated with this Software
- All roadmap documents, technical specifications, session notes, and prompt engineering content
- The name "GasPi-Check", the tagline "L'intelligence collective au service de la décarbonation alimentaire", the name "Zen-Eco", and all associated branding

### 1.2 Copyright Protection
This Software is protected under:
- French intellectual property law, including the **Code de la propriété intellectuelle** (CPI), Articles L111-1 et seq.
- European Union Directive 2009/24/EC on the legal protection of computer programs
- The **Berne Convention for the Protection of Literary and Artistic Works** (applicable in 179 countries)
- The **TRIPS Agreement** (Agreement on Trade-Related Aspects of Intellectual Property Rights)
- The **WIPO Copyright Treaty (WCT)**
- United States copyright law (17 U.S.C. § 101 et seq.) to the extent applicable

### 1.3 Trade Secret Protection
The business logic, data monetization strategy, behavioral analytics pipeline, and associated commercial intelligence contained within or described by this Software constitute **trade secrets** protected under:
- French law on trade secrets (**Loi n° 2018-670** transposing EU Directive 2016/943)
- EU Directive 2016/943 on the protection of undisclosed know-how and business information
- The **Defend Trade Secrets Act (DTSA)** to the extent applicable internationally

