**(c) Modification and Derivative Works** — Modifying, adapting, translating, transforming, or creating derivative works based on the Software or any of its constituent elements, including but not limited to its algorithms, data structures, gamification logic, or architectural patterns.

**(d) Reverse Engineering** — Reverse engineering, decompiling, disassembling, or otherwise attempting to derive the source code, underlying algorithms, or logic from any compiled or deployed version of the Software.

**(e) Commercial Exploitation** — Using any portion of the Software, its concepts, its business strategies, its data monetization models, or its technical architecture for any commercial purpose whatsoever.

**(f) Competitive Use** — Using any knowledge, concepts, architectural patterns, or business insights derived from the Software to build, develop, or improve any competing product or service, whether directly or indirectly.

**(g) Data Pipeline Replication** — Replicating, adapting, or implementing the Barcode Analytics pipeline, the behavioral data collection methodology, the EAN-level indexing strategy, or the data monetization approach described in or associated with the Software.

**(h) Sublicensing** — Sublicensing, renting, leasing, lending, or otherwise transferring any purported rights in the Software to any third party.

**(i) Circumvention** — Circumventing, disabling, or otherwise interfering with any technical protection measures or access controls applied to the Software.

**(j) Misrepresentation** — Representing to any person or entity that you have any right, license, or authorization with respect to the Software.

