## ARTICLE 3 — ENFORCEMENT AND REMEDIES

### 3.1 Infringement
Any violation of this Agreement constitutes an infringement of the Owner's intellectual property rights and will be pursued to the fullest extent permitted by law.

### 3.2 Legal Remedies
In the event of any unauthorized use, reproduction, distribution, or other infringement, the Owner reserves the right to seek and shall be entitled to:

**(a) Injunctive Relief** — Immediate preliminary and permanent injunctive relief, without the need to post a bond or other security, to stop the infringing activity. The Owner expressly acknowledges that monetary damages may be inadequate to compensate for certain infringements and that injunctive relief is an appropriate remedy.

**(b) Actual Damages** — Full compensation for all actual damages suffered by the Owner, including lost profits, lost business opportunities, and any diminution in the value of the Software or associated business assets.

**(c) Statutory Damages** — Where applicable under French law (CPI Article L335-2 et seq.) or any other applicable jurisdiction, statutory damages for copyright infringement, which may amount to up to **300,000 euros** per act of infringement under French law, and up to **150,000 USD** per work infringed under US law (17 U.S.C. § 504).

**(d) Criminal Penalties** — Under French law, willful copyright infringement (contrefaçon) is a criminal offense punishable by up to **3 years imprisonment and €300,000 in fines** (CPI Article L335-2). For infringement committed by an organized group, penalties may reach **5 years imprisonment and €500,000 in fines** (CPI Article L335-4).

**(e) Attorney's Fees and Costs** — Full recovery of all legal fees, court costs, expert fees, and any other costs incurred in enforcing this Agreement.

**(f) Disgorgement of Profits** — Recovery of all profits derived by the infringer from the unauthorized use of the Software.

**(g) Enhanced Damages** — Where infringement is found to be willful, the Owner reserves the right to seek enhanced or punitive damages to the maximum extent permitted by applicable law.

### 3.3 Trade Secret Misappropriation
Any unauthorized acquisition, disclosure, or use of the trade secrets contained in or associated with this Software shall constitute misappropriation under applicable law, including French law (Loi n° 2018-670) and the EU Trade Secrets Directive (2016/943), and shall expose the infringer to:
- Civil liability for all damages resulting from the misappropriation
- Criminal liability where applicable
- Injunctive relief to prevent further disclosure or use

### 3.4 No Statute of Limitations Waiver
The Owner expressly reserves all rights to pursue infringement claims at any time permitted by applicable law and does not waive any right by delay in enforcement.

